00:41:32.948 --> 00:41:34.867
Too many tax dollars
to try and hide.

766
00:41:35.034 --> 00:41:37.369
and-and off-world artifacts
are too profitable

767
00:41:37.536 --> 00:41:39.121
to leave in the hands
of appointed officials.

768
00:41:39.330 --> 00:41:42.041
especially after
the Nixon thing.

769
00:41:42.166 --> 00:41:45.753
Presidents are civilians again
after eight years. so...

770
00:41:45.878 --> 00:41:49.173
so there's no longer a reason
to read them in on any of this.

771
00:41:51.175 --> 00:41:54.512
I was a part of all that
until I saw what you just saw.

772
00:41:55.596 --> 00:41:59.058
This all stops now.

773
00:41:59.141 --> 00:42:00.726
What are you gonna do?

774
00:42:01.769 --> 00:42:06.440
Full disclosure
to the whole world all at once.

775
00:42:09.193 --> 00:42:12.154
Have you considered
what effect that'll have?

776
00:42:13.280 --> 00:42:15.032
On everything?

777
00:42:16.033 --> 00:42:17.368
What...

778
00:42:17.493 --> 00:42:19.203
It's not up to me
to decide if it's...

779
00:42:19.245 --> 00:42:22.081
if it's good or bad
for people to know.

780
00:42:22.289 --> 00:42:25.000
Then how is it up to you
to decide that the right to know

781
00:42:25.084 --> 00:42:27.378
outweighs the consequences
of knowing?

782
00:42:27.503 --> 00:42:29.255
Are you saying
we leave this up to WARDEX?

783
00:42:29.338 --> 00:42:31.757
'Cause they-they've already
decided this belongs to them.

784
00:42:31.882 --> 00:42:34.510
this core truth
about the universe.

785
00:42:34.635 --> 00:42:36.887
-It's wrong.
-You can't do that.

786
00:42:38.013 --> 00:42:39.723
Think about...

787
00:42:41.308 --> 00:42:42.685
People will see them as deities.

788
00:42:42.768 --> 00:42:44.812
They'll stop believing in God.

789
00:42:44.853 --> 00:42:46.689
Well. you left the church.

790
00:42:46.814 --> 00:42:48.148
Not because I stopped believing.

791
00:42:48.232 --> 00:42:49.817
because I could no longer say
with certainty

792
00:42:49.984 --> 00:42:51.235
that God is divine.

793
00:42:51.360 --> 00:42:54.572
but I believe profoundly
that he's essential.

794
00:42:56.323 --> 00:42:57.783
He's how we define ourselves.

795
00:42:57.950 --> 00:43:00.911
He's what keeps
whole civilizations together.

796
00:43:02.288 --> 00:43:05.082
We've been raised to believe
in a supreme being.

797
00:43:05.207 --> 00:43:08.961
and now you want to show us
actual supreme beings?

798
00:43:09.044 --> 00:43:10.879
People can't handle both.

799
00:43:13.340 --> 00:43:14.967
Of course they can.

800
00:43:15.175 --> 00:43:16.594
No. they can't.

801
00:43:17.595 --> 00:43:19.680
Look at our history
with any sudden change.

802
00:43:20.681 --> 00:43:25.019
And now. with the world about
to blow up in all our faces?

803
00:43:26.478 --> 00:43:31.066
You'll get panic and-and chaos.
and God help us.

804
00:43:35.237 --> 00:43:37.448
Hugo's expecting me to check in.

805
00:43:49.168 --> 00:43:50.919
No signal.

806
00:43:52.671 --> 00:43:54.298
No signal.

807
00:43:54.465 --> 00:43:56.717
I'll try the other side
of the hill.

808
00:44:26.622 --> 00:44:27.790
Okay.

809
00:44:27.998 --> 00:44:29.249
Unlock the door!

810
00:44:29.416 --> 00:44:30.626
-What?
-Jackson. come on!

811
00:44:30.668 --> 00:44:32.461
Oh. shit. Sorry.

812
00:44:33.587 --> 00:44:35.255
Oh. sorry. sorry.

813
00:44:35.422 --> 00:44:37.841
-Okay.
-Oh. my God.

814
00:44:43.681 --> 00:44:45.140
If you answer that in French.
I swear to God

815
00:44:45.265 --> 00:44:46.517
I'm marching you
right back inside.

816
00:44:46.725 --> 00:44:48.227
Hello?

817
00:44:48.310 --> 00:44:50.187
I've been
waiting a very long time

818
00:44:50.270 --> 00:44:52.481
to meet you. Ms. Fairchild.

819
00:44:52.606 --> 00:44:54.024
Who is this?

820
00:44:54.191 --> 00:44:55.859
A friend.

821
00:44:56.985 --> 00:44:59.738
And if I'm right about you.
Margaret.

822
00:44:59.822 --> 00:45:01.323
you'd know if I wasn't.

823
00:45:01.448 --> 00:45:02.783
No. I don't... I don't know you

824
00:45:02.866 --> 00:45:04.618
any more than I know
what's happening to me.

825
00:45:04.785 --> 00:45:06.912
Very few people could
manage this as well as you.

826
00:45:07.079 --> 00:45:08.831
-I'm not managing it. I'm not.
-Who-who is that?

827
00:45:08.872 --> 00:45:11.291
I am frightened.
I'm frightened out of my wits.

828
00:45:11.417 --> 00:45:15.379
Because you're just a passenger
on your way somewhere.

829
00:45:15.504 --> 00:45:17.256
-Let us help you get there.
-Help me how?

830
00:45:17.297 --> 00:45:18.298
What do you mean?

831
00:45:18.424 --> 00:45:19.717
-Is that the FBI?
-Shh!

832
00:45:19.925 --> 00:45:20.968
We want to offer you
our protection.

833
00:45:21.135 --> 00:45:22.511
We held back on reaching out

834
00:45:22.594 --> 00:45:24.596
until after we saw
your weather report.

835
00:45:24.763 --> 00:45:25.889
You held back?

836
00:45:26.056 --> 00:45:27.141
What do you mean?
What does that mean?

837
00:45:27.307 --> 00:45:29.184
Are you gonna need a lawyer?

838
00:45:32.813 --> 00:45:35.816
Who is 873-2626?

839
00:45:37.317 --> 00:45:38.694
Since you know that number.

840
00:45:38.777 --> 00:45:41.238
you must already know
who it belongs to.

841
00:45:43.532 --> 00:45:44.867
Kellner?

842
00:45:45.784 --> 00:45:46.702
Kellner?

843
00:45:46.785 --> 00:45:48.620
All right.

844
00:45:48.662 --> 00:45:50.164
Listen carefully.

845
00:45:50.330 --> 00:45:51.582
You cannot go home.

846
00:45:51.707 --> 00:45:52.916
If you have another direction
in mind.

847
00:45:53.041 --> 00:45:55.252
even a vague inclination.
follow it.

848
00:45:55.461 --> 00:45:57.087
If we can find you by phone.
others can

849
00:45:57.254 --> 00:45:58.881
-find you in the world.
-No. it's too late.

850
00:45:59.047 --> 00:46:00.382
They...
Uh. they already found me.

851
00:46:00.466 --> 00:46:03.177
Hang up immediately.
Destroy your phone.

852
00:46:03.385 --> 00:46:04.720
How will you find me?

853
00:46:04.845 --> 00:46:06.054
I have every confidence
you'll find us.

854
00:46:06.138 --> 00:46:07.264
Do it now.

855
00:46:09.016 --> 00:46:11.894
Wait. wait. What are you...
Wh-What are you doing?!

856
00:46:13.395 --> 00:46:14.313
Back up over the phone.

857
00:46:14.480 --> 00:46:16.106
-What?
-Back up!

858
00:46:16.190 --> 00:46:17.775
-Come on. -Okay. I'd like
to point out that I'm being

859
00:46:17.858 --> 00:46:20.194
extremely cool here
and that I'm rolling with it.

860
00:46:20.402 --> 00:46:22.446
and that was a $600 phone.

861
00:46:23.363 --> 00:46:25.324
Well. it's still a $600 phone
'cause you missed it.

862
00:46:25.491 --> 00:46:26.867
Jackson. pull forward
till you hear the crunch.

863
00:46:26.992 --> 00:46:28.076
-Come on.
-Sorry.

864
00:46:32.498 --> 00:46:34.666
Oh. my God. you missed it again.
Oh. my God.

865
00:46:34.750 --> 00:46:36.877
-Okay.
-What?

866
00:46:40.506 --> 00:46:41.965
Okay.

867
00:46:43.592 --> 00:46:46.053
Pull forward. Go. go. go.

868
00:46:47.596 --> 00:46:49.431
Keep going. Keep going.

869
00:46:58.649 --> 00:47:00.943
Okay. Okay.

870
00:47:01.026 --> 00:47:04.196
-Okay. let's go. Let's go.
-Uh... wh-where?

871
00:47:04.363 --> 00:47:05.948
-North.
-Why?

872
00:47:06.031 --> 00:47:07.324
Because that's where
Daniel Kellner is.

873
00:47:07.449 --> 00:47:08.867
Oh. my God.

874
00:47:08.992 --> 00:47:10.577
Who is this dude?
Is he some guy from your past

875
00:47:10.702 --> 00:47:12.120
-that you never told me about?
-I don't know. Jackson.

876
00:47:12.204 --> 00:47:13.455
-Or what is it?
-You're giving me a headache.

877
00:47:13.580 --> 00:47:14.414
I don't know
what I'm doing here.

878
00:47:14.581 --> 00:47:15.707
I don't know who he is.

879
00:47:15.791 --> 00:47:17.209
I just know
he's someplace north.

880
00:47:17.376 --> 00:47:18.460
That's all I know. okay?

881
00:47:18.585 --> 00:47:20.003
Oh. my God. What is that sound?

882
00:47:22.339 --> 00:47:24.383
-Your hailstorm.
-Wow.

883
00:47:24.591 --> 00:47:25.884
Weather Shimmy?

884
00:47:26.009 --> 00:47:28.345
Just drive. Just drive.

885
00:48:16.810 --> 00:48:19.396
You got Kellner on 2626.

886
00:48:21.064 --> 00:48:22.524
Look at the video
I just sent you.

887
00:48:22.691 --> 00:48:24.192
Okay. hold on.

888
00:48:30.574 --> 00:48:31.992
Yeah. So?

889
00:48:32.117 --> 00:48:33.994
She's the one
we've been waiting for.

890
00:48:34.119 --> 00:48:36.413
Her? Why?

891
00:48:36.538 --> 00:48:38.749
Did you not hear her?

892
00:48:38.874 --> 00:48:40.334
Yeah. I heard her.

893
00:48:40.459 --> 00:48:41.752
And you still ask why?

894
00:48:41.919 --> 00:48:43.670
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

895
00:48:43.712 --> 00:48:45.589
That's all she had to say?

896
00:48:46.924 --> 00:48:49.009
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

897
00:48:49.134 --> 00:48:50.344
That's what she said?

898
00:48:50.510 --> 00:48:52.095
You didn't hear it?

899
00:48:53.555 --> 00:48:55.057
We all heard it.

900
00:48:55.140 --> 00:48:57.225
We couldn't understand it.
It's not English.

901
00:48:57.392 --> 00:48:58.894
Of course it is.

902
00:48:59.061 --> 00:49:00.979
I'm listening to it right now.

903
00:49:01.146 --> 00:49:02.898
I'm sending you to Kansas City.
where she's from.

904
00:49:03.023 --> 00:49:04.816
-We'll get a car to you.
Leave tonight. -Hey. wait.

905
00:49:05.025 --> 00:49:06.568
-Wait a second. Wait a second.
-Do not travel by day.

906
00:49:06.693 --> 00:49:07.945
You're not hearing it?
It's-it's perfectly clear.

907
00:49:08.070 --> 00:49:09.071
Detour past tollbooths
and turnpikes.

908
00:49:09.237 --> 00:49:10.364
Hey. listen to me.

909
00:49:10.405 --> 00:49:11.657
Have you played this
to other people?

910
00:49:11.823 --> 00:49:13.784
Stay with me.

911
00:49:13.867 --> 00:49:16.453
A motel room key will be
in the car with directions.

912
00:49:16.578 --> 00:49:18.413
Santiago will retrieve you
in the morning.

913
00:49:18.538 --> 00:49:20.958
By then. I'll know
what comes next.

914
00:49:21.124 --> 00:49:23.752
Hugo. you're scaring
the shit out of me.

915
00:49:23.877 --> 00:49:27.422
There are two of you. Daniel.

916
00:49:27.506 --> 00:49:30.676
There's always been
just the two of you.

917
00:52:26.059 --> 00:52:27.602
Hello. Jane.

918
00:52:27.644 --> 00:52:29.604
Please.

919
00:52:30.897 --> 00:52:32.983
Have a seat.

920
00:52:38.572 --> 00:52:41.074
Where are you right now. Jane?

921
00:52:41.283 --> 00:52:42.993
What is your location?

922
00:52:44.161 --> 00:52:46.621
-I don't know.
-Relax. please.

923
00:52:49.958 --> 00:52:52.502
-Who are you?
-I'll ask the questions.

924
00:52:53.503 --> 00:52:55.338
Are you still with
Daniel Kellner?

925
00:53:01.428 --> 00:53:02.846
He's outside.

926
00:53:06.474 --> 00:53:08.143
Where were you last night?

927
00:53:17.611 --> 00:53:20.280
-BP's high but holding: 156/94.
-O2's decent at 96.

928
00:53:20.405 --> 00:53:22.199
-but sodium's climbing.
-Heart rate's hot. too-- 118.

929
00:53:22.365 --> 00:53:23.491
-Potassium's borderline. too.
-Jane!

930
00:53:23.617 --> 00:53:25.202
-Stand by. Ringer's.
-Jane!

931
00:53:26.119 --> 00:53:27.621
Jane!

932
00:53:27.662 --> 00:53:30.040
Where were you last night?

933
00:53:31.208 --> 00:53:34.169
Monastery of St. Clare
of the Dawn.

934
00:53:34.294 --> 00:53:36.421
Monastery St. Clare?

935
00:53:36.546 --> 00:53:37.881
Of course.

936
00:53:38.006 --> 00:53:41.009
I remember St. Clare
from my Sunday school.

937
00:53:41.092 --> 00:53:43.011
She was too sick to go
to midnight Mass.

938
00:53:43.178 --> 00:53:45.722
and she had a vision
of it instead.

939
00:53:45.889 --> 00:53:48.516
She was in two places at once.
like me.

940
00:53:51.186 --> 00:53:53.188
Monastery of St. Clare. Got it.

941
00:53:53.313 --> 00:53:55.232
13 miles southeast
of the District.

942
00:53:55.398 --> 00:53:57.901
When you left.
which way did you drive?

943
00:54:01.529 --> 00:54:02.781
I don't know.

944
00:54:02.906 --> 00:54:04.532
Was the sun up?

945
00:54:07.577 --> 00:54:08.912
Yes.

946
00:54:09.079 --> 00:54:11.331
Did you drive into it
or away from it?

947
00:54:14.668 --> 00:54:16.419
It was on the right.

948
00:54:18.505 --> 00:54:19.923
I don't like you.

949
00:54:20.048 --> 00:54:21.800
Not required.

950
00:54:21.925 --> 00:54:23.260
Sun on the right.

951
00:54:23.385 --> 00:54:25.178
Sun on the right--
they're headed due north.

952
00:54:25.303 --> 00:54:26.429
possibly northwest.

953
00:54:26.596 --> 00:54:28.348
Could be on 27. 18
or the interstate.

954
00:54:28.473 --> 00:54:29.766
Interstate not likely.

955
00:54:29.933 --> 00:54:31.559
Focus on frontage roads
or county highways.

956
00:54:31.685 --> 00:54:34.145
Did you pass a street sign?

957
00:54:34.312 --> 00:54:35.772
Yes.

958
00:54:35.855 --> 00:54:37.607
What did it say?

959
00:54:41.861 --> 00:54:45.115
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

960
00:54:45.156 --> 00:54:47.659
Street sign.
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

961
00:54:47.784 --> 00:54:50.287
I've got half
a dozen towns off the 26.

962
00:54:50.453 --> 00:54:53.665
Silver Hollow. Oakshade.
Ironmere. Stonemont...

963
00:54:53.707 --> 00:54:55.667
Try for more details. Jane.

964
00:54:55.750 --> 00:54:57.294
What else did you pass?

965
00:54:59.170 --> 00:55:00.297
A river.

966
00:55:00.380 --> 00:55:01.965
Passed a river.

967
00:55:02.090 --> 00:55:04.259
Did you see a sign for a town
after that?

968
00:55:06.344 --> 00:55:08.596
-Yes.
-What did it say?

969
00:55:13.059 --> 00:55:14.561
S-Sykesville.

970
00:55:14.728 --> 00:55:17.480
-Sykesville.
-Sykesville.

971
00:55:18.648 --> 00:55:21.109
Field is narrowed.
Track and converge.

972
00:55:21.234 --> 00:55:23.862
Charlie 27. take the lead.
You're four miles out.

973
00:55:23.945 --> 00:55:26.197
Maintain maximum legal speed.

974
00:55:26.406 --> 00:55:29.242
How soon after you saw the sign
did you make a turn?

975
00:55:29.367 --> 00:55:30.952
-A few minutes.
-Few minutes.

976
00:55:31.077 --> 00:55:32.912
Did you turn right or left?

977
00:55:33.079 --> 00:55:34.581
-Right.
-Right.

978
00:55:34.706 --> 00:55:37.334
Do you remember
the name of the road?

979
00:55:37.500 --> 00:55:38.668
No.

980
00:55:38.877 --> 00:55:40.837
Do you remember anything
about the road?

981
00:55:49.429 --> 00:55:51.139
It was a dirt road.

982
00:55:51.222 --> 00:55:52.682
Dirt road.

983
00:55:52.849 --> 00:55:54.476
Ash Hollow Road.
three and a quarter miles

984
00:55:54.642 --> 00:55:56.770
outside Sykesville. dead end.

985
00:55:56.978 --> 00:55:58.396
Farmhouse at the end.

986
00:55:58.563 --> 00:55:59.856
And found it.

987
00:55:59.939 --> 00:56:01.274
Ash Hollow Road.

988
00:56:01.441 --> 00:56:03.693
Target is a farmhouse.

989
00:56:10.450 --> 00:56:12.786
You've done very well. Jane.

990
00:56:12.827 --> 00:56:15.372
A service to your country.

991
00:56:15.580 --> 00:56:18.708
But I have to ask you
one more thing.

992
00:56:18.917 --> 00:56:23.004
If we can't find Daniel
or we miss him again.

993
00:56:23.046 --> 00:56:25.548
you may need
to stop him yourself

994
00:56:25.632 --> 00:56:27.634
any way you can.

995
00:56:34.057 --> 00:56:36.017
Hang on. BP just tanked.
88 on 62.

996
00:56:36.101 --> 00:56:38.061
Uh. heart rate's dropping--
down to 59.

997
00:56:38.144 --> 00:56:41.064
Uh. O2 is 93 and falling. 91.

998
00:56:45.693 --> 00:56:47.612
92 on 60 and holding.
O2's still dropping. though.

999
00:56:47.821 --> 00:56:48.738
Let's start bagging.

1000
00:56:48.863 --> 00:56:50.031
Make sure you secure the airway.

1001
00:56:50.240 --> 00:56:52.867
High 80s. Keep going.

1002
00:56:52.909 --> 00:56:54.911
Get away!

1003
00:57:00.291 --> 00:57:02.085
Jane.

1004
00:57:03.086 --> 00:57:06.256
What Daniel is trying to do
is wrong.

1005
00:57:06.339 --> 00:57:08.800
It's dangerous.

1006
00:57:08.883 --> 00:57:12.262
It would tip the balance in
an already destabilized world.

1007
00:57:13.179 --> 00:57:14.431
Yes.

1008
00:57:14.597 --> 00:57:16.683
Jane. could you stop him
if you had to?

1009
00:57:16.766 --> 00:57:19.686
No. No.

1010
00:57:22.522 --> 00:57:25.483
"Father. if you be willing.

1011
00:57:25.567 --> 00:57:28.611
"let this cup pass me by.

1012
00:57:28.736 --> 00:57:31.906
Yet not as I will.
but as you will."

1013
00:57:32.073 --> 00:57:34.534
And what did Christ say next?

1014
00:57:36.119 --> 00:57:38.580
"By my will.
thine will be done."

1015
00:57:39.581 --> 00:57:43.042
If the moment comes.
I'll be with you.

1016
00:57:43.209 --> 00:57:45.044
and you'll act. Jane.

1017
00:57:45.211 --> 00:57:48.882
out of love for Daniel.
out of love for the human race.

1018
00:57:52.093 --> 00:57:53.887
Now look around the room.

1019
00:57:54.971 --> 00:57:56.431
Slowly.

1020
00:57:59.893 --> 00:58:01.144
Left to right.

1021
00:58:04.355 --> 00:58:05.815
Stop there.

1022
00:58:07.150 --> 00:58:08.735
Get up.

