-I have to.
-You don't have to go so...

1275
01:22:56.054 --> 01:22:58.014
-Yeah. uh. yeah. I do.
-Uh. you're enjoying this.

1276
01:22:58.098 --> 01:23:00.642
Yeah. I mean. it-it feels good.
It feels good. and then...

1277
01:23:00.809 --> 01:23:02.644
Yeah. but-but... but you know.
You know.

1278
01:23:02.852 --> 01:23:04.354
I mean. you've been driving
like a maniac

1279
01:23:04.396 --> 01:23:05.814
the last few days. you know.

1280
01:23:05.939 --> 01:23:07.691
-How do you know that?
-I just know things.

1281
01:23:07.774 --> 01:23:09.401
It's just. something happened
to me a couple of days ago.

1282
01:23:09.442 --> 01:23:11.319
and now I-I know things.

1283
01:23:11.486 --> 01:23:12.654
Things I don't really
want to know.

1284
01:23:12.821 --> 01:23:13.989
and all the things
I do want to know.

1285
01:23:14.072 --> 01:23:15.323
I don't really know at all.

1286
01:23:15.490 --> 01:23:16.825
so I've just been
kind of rolling with it.

1287
01:23:16.866 --> 01:23:18.576
You know. like...
Oh. wow. you were in jail?

1288
01:23:18.660 --> 01:23:20.328
-That must have been so...
-Hey. hey!

1289
01:23:20.412 --> 01:23:22.080
You see what I mean?

1290
01:23:22.122 --> 01:23:24.290
It's crazy. It's crazy.

1291
01:23:24.416 --> 01:23:28.169
I look at somebody.
and I just drop in on them.

1292
01:23:29.170 --> 01:23:31.840
It's like. for a few seconds.
I am them.

1293
01:23:31.965 --> 01:23:33.508
I see the things
that they've lived.

1294
01:23:33.675 --> 01:23:35.760
It's just like
it's all happening to me. too.

1295
01:23:35.885 --> 01:23:37.178
You know. like-like...

1296
01:23:37.303 --> 01:23:38.680
like right now
your shoulder's killing you.

1297
01:23:38.847 --> 01:23:40.598
Yeah. and you-you just
want to yell.

1298
01:23:40.724 --> 01:23:42.142
-"Keep your eyes on the road!"
-Keep your eyes on the road!

1299
01:23:42.225 --> 01:23:43.893
I know. and you can't stop
thinking about Jane.

1300
01:23:44.019 --> 01:23:45.145
and Jane should be back
at the Monastery St. Clare.

1301
01:23:45.186 --> 01:23:46.521
-You're absolutely right.
-Jane?

1302
01:23:46.688 --> 01:23:49.315
But then yesterday.
I'm driving with Jackson.

1303
01:23:49.399 --> 01:23:51.359
and I flashed on you
without seeing you.

1304
01:23:51.568 --> 01:23:52.944
It was so strong.

1305
01:23:53.153 --> 01:23:54.654
I dropped right in on you

1306
01:23:54.779 --> 01:23:56.239
without even needing
to look at you. and that was

1307
01:23:56.448 --> 01:23:58.116
the first time that crazy shit
has ever happened to me.

1308
01:23:58.158 --> 01:23:59.743
How long you been able
to do this?

1309
01:23:59.951 --> 01:24:01.077
Since yesterday.

1310
01:24:01.202 --> 01:24:02.829
Since the bird.

1311
01:24:02.996 --> 01:24:04.456
-What bird?
-This-this bird.

1312
01:24:04.497 --> 01:24:06.082
Flew in through my window.

1313
01:24:06.249 --> 01:24:08.043
It was beautiful. I looked
at it. and then it-it...

1314
01:24:08.084 --> 01:24:09.127
Was it a cardinal?

1315
01:24:09.294 --> 01:24:10.503
Holy sh... How the...

1316
01:24:10.670 --> 01:24:12.047
You're freaking me the fuck out.

1317
01:24:18.136 --> 01:24:19.471
I was 20. I was in college.

1318
01:24:19.596 --> 01:24:21.431
You were flunking out.
basically. right?

1319
01:24:21.473 --> 01:24:22.891
Yeah. I-I was pretty smart.

1320
01:24:23.016 --> 01:24:24.184
You were. but it was
the partying.

1321
01:24:24.350 --> 01:24:25.351
It was the partying
and the drugs.

1322
01:24:25.518 --> 01:24:26.936
I mean. ketamine? Come on. dude.

1323
01:24:27.103 --> 01:24:28.188
-Could you please stop?
-Sorry. I'm stopping.

1324
01:24:28.354 --> 01:24:29.606
-I was 20. I was in college.
-Yes.

1325
01:24:29.689 --> 01:24:32.233
Uh. it was dark. I-I was in bed.

1326
01:24:32.400 --> 01:24:34.694
and I dreamed that
something was watching me.

1327
01:24:34.819 --> 01:24:36.237
I woke up.
and there was this bird.

1328
01:24:36.404 --> 01:24:37.739
-It was a cardinal.
-In the window.

1329
01:24:37.906 --> 01:24:39.657
and it-it looked at me.
and after that.

1330
01:24:39.866 --> 01:24:41.326
everything just changed.

1331
01:24:41.451 --> 01:24:43.745
I saw things:
context. patterns. artifacting.

1332
01:24:43.828 --> 01:24:45.455
I could see it all.

1333
01:24:45.580 --> 01:24:47.373
Arrays and conditionals
just appeared in my head...

1334
01:24:47.540 --> 01:24:48.958
Fully solved. "If P. then Q."

1335
01:24:49.042 --> 01:24:50.460
Exactly. Solved equations

1336
01:24:50.585 --> 01:24:51.920
-without even thinking...
-And you could read

1337
01:24:52.045 --> 01:24:53.296
eight-bit binary data
like it was English.

1338
01:24:53.421 --> 01:24:54.464
-like it was nothing.
-Yeah.

1339
01:24:54.589 --> 01:24:55.590
How do you know all this?

1340
01:24:55.673 --> 01:24:57.258
I don't. You do.

1341
01:24:57.300 --> 01:24:58.468
God. you hated it.

1342
01:24:58.551 --> 01:25:00.303
-It was a curse.
-Yeah.

1343
01:25:00.386 --> 01:25:02.013
I couldn't relate to anybody.

1344
01:25:02.180 --> 01:25:03.973
I lost every friend I ever had
because I-I couldn't stand

1345
01:25:04.099 --> 01:25:05.600
to be around people.

1346
01:25:05.683 --> 01:25:07.435
Until you met Jane.

1347
01:25:10.897 --> 01:25:12.440
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know."

1348
01:25:12.565 --> 01:25:14.192
-What?
-That's what you said on TV.

1349
01:25:14.275 --> 01:25:15.693
They said I was
talking nonsense.

1350
01:25:15.902 --> 01:25:17.195
I understood every word.

1351
01:25:17.320 --> 01:25:18.947
What happened to us?

1352
01:25:19.072 --> 01:25:20.907
Oh. my God.

1353
01:25:23.201 --> 01:25:24.536
Who is it?!

1354
01:25:27.163 --> 01:25:28.289
Boyd. stop!

1355
01:25:28.414 --> 01:25:29.624
Boyd!

1356
01:25:38.842 --> 01:25:39.926
Shit.

1357
01:25:40.927 --> 01:25:42.428
We got to jump! We got to bail!

1358
01:25:42.595 --> 01:25:44.556
I can't!
I'm standing on the brakes!

1359
01:25:48.601 --> 01:25:50.478
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

1360
01:25:52.564 --> 01:25:53.815
No. no. no. no. no. no. no!

1361
01:25:56.109 --> 01:25:57.819
He's backing up! Get out now!

1362
01:26:11.499 --> 01:26:13.293
All right. all right!

1363
01:26:21.718 --> 01:26:23.303
Get to the ladder!

1364
01:26:29.184 --> 01:26:31.102
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1365
01:26:31.227 --> 01:26:32.478
Okay.

1366
01:27:08.389 --> 01:27:10.475
Go! Jump!

1367
01:27:23.363 --> 01:27:25.156
You got to jump!

1368
01:27:26.074 --> 01:27:27.575
Jump! Now!

1369
01:28:02.193 --> 01:28:03.611
Oh. my God.

1370
01:28:11.703 --> 01:28:14.539
I can't breathe.
I can't breathe.

1371
01:28:15.373 --> 01:28:16.874
I can't breathe.

1372
01:28:18.167 --> 01:28:20.295
-It's okay. It's okay.
-I can't breathe.

1373
01:28:20.420 --> 01:28:22.005
-I think you're having
a panic attack. -Oh. my God.

1374
01:28:22.130 --> 01:28:24.173
-It's okay. It's okay.
-Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1375
01:28:24.340 --> 01:28:26.050
-It's okay. I'm used to 'em.
-My hands.

1376
01:28:26.134 --> 01:28:27.885
-We're okay.
-It's like my dad.

1377
01:28:28.052 --> 01:28:29.512
-It's like my dad. My hands.
-No. no. no. No. no. no. no.

1378
01:28:29.637 --> 01:28:31.472
It's like Parkinson's.
It's like Parkinson's.

1379
01:28:31.639 --> 01:28:32.890
It's not the same thing.
It's not that.

1380
01:28:32.932 --> 01:28:34.475
Yes. it is. It's the same.

1381
01:28:34.559 --> 01:28:36.436
No. he couldn't control it.
I can't control it.

1382
01:28:36.477 --> 01:28:37.979
-I can't control it.
-You can.

1383
01:28:38.104 --> 01:28:40.732
Oh. my God.
I ran away from him.

1384
01:28:40.898 --> 01:28:43.609
-I didn't want to be around
him anymore. -No. no. no. Stop.

1385
01:28:43.735 --> 01:28:45.486
-I want this gone!
-Okay.

1386
01:28:45.653 --> 01:28:48.406
I just want it gone!
I want it gone!

1387
01:28:48.531 --> 01:28:50.992
I want it gone! I just have
no mind of my own anymore!

1388
01:28:51.159 --> 01:28:53.077
Okay. stop! Stop!
Stop talking! Stop.

1389
01:28:53.202 --> 01:28:54.245
Give me your hands.

1390
01:28:54.329 --> 01:28:55.580
-Okay. look at me.
-No. no. no.

1391
01:28:55.621 --> 01:28:56.914
-Look at me.
-I-I'm gonna see things.

1392
01:28:56.998 --> 01:28:58.708
-I'm gonna see things. Please.
-Okay.

1393
01:28:58.750 --> 01:28:59.751
Breathe through your nose.
Breathe through your nose.

1394
01:29:01.461 --> 01:29:03.087
That's it. Okay.

1395
01:29:03.212 --> 01:29:05.131
I can't feel my hands.

1396
01:29:05.256 --> 01:29:07.091
Okay. Okay.

1397
01:29:07.216 --> 01:29:08.885
Okay. give me your hands.
Come on.

1398
01:29:08.968 --> 01:29:10.636
Come on. Put your hands there.

1399
01:29:10.803 --> 01:29:12.597
Feel that. Okay. you feel that?

1400
01:29:12.764 --> 01:29:14.390
I'm here. I'm here.

1401
01:29:14.515 --> 01:29:15.892
We're here.

1402
01:29:15.975 --> 01:29:17.643
-We're okay.
-Okay.

1403
01:29:18.770 --> 01:29:20.146
-We're okay.
-We're okay.

1404
01:29:20.271 --> 01:29:22.398
We're okay.

1405
01:29:22.440 --> 01:29:25.234
We're okay now. You're okay.

1406
01:29:29.614 --> 01:29:31.657
We're okay.

1407
01:29:31.741 --> 01:29:33.034
Okay.

1408
01:29:37.747 --> 01:29:39.624
Thank you.

1409
01:29:42.585 --> 01:29:44.921
Kellner called in from a gas
station outside Mount Leonard.

1410
01:29:45.004 --> 01:29:46.255
I'll meet Santiago and his crew.

1411
01:29:46.339 --> 01:29:48.466
We can be there
in a couple hours.

1412
01:29:51.052 --> 01:29:53.221
H-Hugo?

1413
01:29:53.346 --> 01:29:54.722
Could everyone leave
the staging area

1414
01:29:54.847 --> 01:29:56.224
for a minute. please?

1415
01:29:56.307 --> 01:29:59.143
-Now. please! Out!
-Yeah. Okay. let's go.

1416
01:30:05.525 --> 01:30:07.193
Hello. Hugo.

1417
01:30:12.782 --> 01:30:14.951
Noah. please.

1418
01:30:15.952 --> 01:30:17.829
It's terribly misguided for you
to dive with that thing.

1419
01:30:17.995 --> 01:30:19.747
It's not a magic wand.

1420
01:30:19.956 --> 01:30:21.749
And it's not a weapon.
but it has functions

1421
01:30:21.833 --> 01:30:24.710
very far beyond
your limited use of it.

1422
01:30:24.794 --> 01:30:29.298
Kellner was an experiencer.
wasn't he?

1423
01:30:29.382 --> 01:30:31.384
That's why
I couldn't dive on him.

1424
01:30:31.467 --> 01:30:33.678
Yes.

1425
01:30:33.761 --> 01:30:35.680
He was.

1426
01:30:37.432 --> 01:30:41.561
And In Vivo 17
told you to recruit him?

1427
01:30:42.728 --> 01:30:44.564
Not in any way you'd understand.

1428
01:30:44.730 --> 01:30:46.274
If this is all their plan. Hugo.

1429
01:30:46.357 --> 01:30:48.776
you can be sure it's
in their interests. not ours.

1430
01:30:48.943 --> 01:30:51.404
That's a very lonely way
to look at the world.

1431
01:30:51.529 --> 01:30:52.905
No. don't condescend to me.

1432
01:30:53.030 --> 01:30:54.407
I'm listening to you. Noah.

1433
01:30:54.490 --> 01:30:56.534
Something I've learned
quite a bit about.

1434
01:30:56.659 --> 01:30:58.119
From your friends?

1435
01:30:58.286 --> 01:30:59.829
Yes.

1436
01:30:59.871 --> 01:31:02.748
They regard empathy
as an evolutionary advantage.

1437
01:31:02.832 --> 01:31:05.418
as the foremost
evolutionary advantage.

1438
01:31:05.501 --> 01:31:09.422
in fact. the core
of animate existence.

1439
01:31:09.630 --> 01:31:11.757
Our rejection
of this understanding

1440
01:31:11.883 --> 01:31:14.010
is leading us to our extinction.

1441
01:31:15.052 --> 01:31:18.139
And is your bleeding heart
why you helped it escape?

1442
01:31:20.057 --> 01:31:21.559
Five years ago.

1443
01:31:21.767 --> 01:31:23.728
That was you. wasn't it?

1444
01:31:25.354 --> 01:31:26.731
Yes.

1445
01:31:27.773 --> 01:31:30.735
The utter insanity
of that act aside.

1446
01:31:30.860 --> 01:31:33.112
how could you lie to me
for five years

1447
01:31:33.196 --> 01:31:34.822
every time you walked
through the door?

1448
01:31:34.906 --> 01:31:37.742
Everything you said to me.
it was all diversion.

1449
01:31:39.619 --> 01:31:42.788
When precisely did you lose
your bearings?

1450
01:31:42.955 --> 01:31:45.333
Around the time you lost yours.

1451
01:31:47.835 --> 01:31:49.420
When you lost her.

1452
01:31:53.674 --> 01:31:56.260
You lost her and almost
immediately were lost to me.

1453
01:31:56.469 --> 01:31:57.720
Because you shut down.

1454
01:31:57.803 --> 01:31:59.138
Do not presume to know me.

1455
01:31:59.305 --> 01:32:00.640
When she died.
you reduced everyone

1456
01:32:00.806 --> 01:32:02.308
to need-to-know. including me.

1457
01:32:02.433 --> 01:32:03.643
Because you were very clear.

1458
01:32:03.768 --> 01:32:05.019
All you needed to know was them.

1459
01:32:05.186 --> 01:32:07.396
and they are not knowable.
not by us.

1460
01:32:07.605 --> 01:32:10.107
They will be.

1461
01:32:10.274 --> 01:32:12.360
In Vivo 17 is nonhuman

1462
01:32:12.485 --> 01:32:14.153
but nearer to God. Noah.
than you or I.

1463
01:32:14.278 --> 01:32:16.322
You don't need to fear them.

1464
01:32:17.240 --> 01:32:19.116
I fear us.

1465
01:32:19.325 --> 01:32:22.245
The entire reason WARDEX exists
is because of our knowledge.

1466
01:32:22.453 --> 01:32:26.541
certain that the human race
cannot accept what we know.

1467
01:32:26.707 --> 01:32:28.417
That truth will upend
all established order

1468
01:32:28.501 --> 01:32:29.669
across the entire world.

1469
01:32:29.835 --> 01:32:32.380
The archive Kellner stole
is a virus

1470
01:32:32.421 --> 01:32:36.634
against which
the world has zero immunity.

1471
01:32:36.717 --> 01:32:39.178
I have spent 35 years
protecting...

1472
01:32:39.303 --> 01:32:40.555
Your own wealth and power--

1473
01:32:40.680 --> 01:32:42.348
that's all
you've been protecting.

1474
01:32:42.473 --> 01:32:45.226
Noah. Noah.

1475
01:32:45.351 --> 01:32:47.520
There is an essential need
in all of us to believe

1476
01:32:47.645 --> 01:32:50.940
and an equal need
to be believed.

1477
01:32:51.065 --> 01:32:53.150
You've violated
every standard of evidence.

1478
01:32:53.276 --> 01:32:54.860
You've infantilized anyone

1479
01:32:54.944 --> 01:32:57.572
who only wanted to understand
what they've witnessed.

1480
01:32:57.780 --> 01:33:00.575
You've brutally stifled
their questions.

1481
01:33:00.616 --> 01:33:03.244
shouted them down.
ridiculed and shamed

1482
01:33:03.369 --> 01:33:05.079
and overridden them
for the crime

1483
01:33:05.162 --> 01:33:07.123
of simply being astonished.

1484
01:33:07.290 --> 01:33:10.042
We believe the believers
and then deny the world

1485
01:33:10.167 --> 01:33:11.961
the chance to believe them. too.

1486
01:33:12.003 --> 01:33:14.589
But people keep wondering.
encountering the unknown.

1487
01:33:14.755 --> 01:33:16.382
telling others
of their experiences.

1488
01:33:16.507 --> 01:33:18.759
They are starved for the truth.

1489
01:33:18.843 --> 01:33:22.388
This 79-year terror campaign

1490
01:33:22.471 --> 01:33:25.933
of obfuscation. lies
and cover-up has to end!

1491
01:33:26.142 --> 01:33:27.977
We're ready to show you
a demonstration.

1492
01:33:28.102 --> 01:33:30.438
-Get out! Get out!
-Sorry. sir. we have...

1493
01:33:30.521 --> 01:33:32.690
Turn around and get out now!

1494
01:33:38.029 --> 01:33:40.948
Pull up the 12 who didn't
show up to work yesterday.

1495
01:33:40.990 --> 01:33:43.951
I need faces
who are with him right now.

1496
01:33:44.076 --> 01:33:46.537
-Her.
-Grace Zhao. neuro-services.

1497
01:33:46.662 --> 01:33:48.247
-Him.
-Nathan Twinning.

1498
01:33:48.331 --> 01:33:49.832
Hugo's chief aide.

1499
01:33:49.957 --> 01:33:51.417
Got a back door
into their mobile providers.

1500
01:33:51.500 --> 01:33:53.294
Hang on.

1501
01:33:56.213 --> 01:34:00.801
They shut down their phones
last night... right here.

1502
01:34:02.011 --> 01:34:03.721
I'll project their routes ahead
to overlap.

1503
01:34:03.929 --> 01:34:06.641
I can give you the AI model
within a quarter-mile radius.

1504
01:34:15.358 --> 01:34:17.902
Sister Maura. Sister.

1505
01:34:26.035 --> 01:34:27.495
Jane?

1506
01:34:27.578 --> 01:34:29.080
Where are you. Jane?

1507
01:34:31.916 --> 01:34:33.376
Does God love us?

1508
01:34:33.542 --> 01:34:36.587
I don't mean. does he love us?
I know he does.

1509
01:34:36.712 --> 01:34:40.341
Does he love only us?

1510
01:34:40.424 --> 01:34:42.677
'Cause Genesis says that
we're his supreme creation.

1511
01:34:42.843 --> 01:34:45.554
but do you think
it's possible that...

1512
01:34:45.638 --> 01:34:47.181
On Earth.

1513
01:34:48.391 --> 01:34:49.517
What?

1514
01:34:49.725 --> 01:34:51.227
Genesis.

1515
01:34:51.352 --> 01:34:56.023
It says we are God's
supreme creation on Earth.

1516
01:35:04.990 --> 01:35:07.201
Do you think
there could be others?

1517
01:35:08.786 --> 01:35:10.871
Yes.

1518
01:35:10.955 --> 01:35:12.540
I would think so.

1519
01:35:12.707 --> 01:35:16.293
Why would he make
such a vast universe.

1520
01:35:16.419 --> 01:35:20.464
yet save it only for us?

1521
01:35:21.549 --> 01:35:26.554
If you found out
we weren't alone. if...

1522
01:35:26.679 --> 01:35:30.349
if someone showed you.
proved it to you...

1523
01:35:32.143 --> 01:35:34.395
...would that frighten you?

1524
01:35:34.520 --> 01:35:37.273
No. Why? Should it?

1525
01:35:37.356 --> 01:35:40.609
But what if it all collapsed?

1526
01:35:40.651 --> 01:35:43.028
For you and every other person
of faith in the world.

1527
01:35:43.112 --> 01:35:44.238
Then what?

1528
01:35:44.280 --> 01:35:45.448
Oh.

1529
01:35:45.656 --> 01:35:47.867
My dear. Jane.

1530
01:35:47.992 --> 01:35:52.913
I don't think that you ever
doubted your belief in God.

1531
01:35:52.955 --> 01:35:56.041
I think you lost your faith
in people.

1532
01:36:00.463 --> 01:36:04.049
They say you're paying because
you borrowed their phone?

1533
01:36:11.223 --> 01:36:12.850
Are you near the computer?

1534
01:36:12.975 --> 01:36:14.477
Yes.

1535
01:36:14.643 --> 01:36:16.854
What is KCXE?

1536
01:36:16.979 --> 01:36:19.607
Just those letters-- KCXE.

1537
01:36:26.906 --> 01:36:28.783
Remember being a kid?

1538
01:36:28.991 --> 01:36:30.409
Sure.

1539
01:36:30.534 --> 01:36:32.953
Mostly stuff after I was ten.

1540
01:36:38.042 --> 01:36:42.129
Can you tell anything about me
from when I was small?

1541
01:37:01.065 --> 01:37:03.150
It's just a fox.

1542
01:37:16.580 --> 01:37:18.123
No. no. no. No!

1543
01:37:18.249 --> 01:37:21.001
-Stop! Stop!
-No. Daniel!

1544
01:37:23.003 --> 01:37:24.380
-Let's go. Come with us.
-Hold on.

1545
01:37:24.463 --> 01:37:26.590
-Hold on.
-Let's go.

1546
01:37:26.674 --> 01:37:28.342
I know him. I know him.

1547
01:37:28.467 --> 01:37:29.844
We just got to check you
real quick.

1548
01:37:30.010 --> 01:37:32.429
make sure nobody's in there
with you.

1549
01:37:39.895 --> 01:37:41.397
Clear.

1550
01:37:41.480 --> 01:37:43.482
All right. let's load up.

1551
01:37:43.649 --> 01:37:45.276
See. the thing about
fire trucks--

1552
01:37:45.359 --> 01:37:47.695
everyone gets the hell
out of your way.

1553
01:38:36.493 --> 01:38:38.245
I knew you'd make it.

1554
01:38:38.287 --> 01:38:39.788
I'm glad you knew.

1555
01:38:39.997 --> 01:38:41.665
Never a doubt.

1556
01:38:48.797 --> 01:38:50.507
Margaret.

1557
01:38:52.092 --> 01:38:53.677
Margaret.

1558
01:38:56.513 --> 01:38:58.015
Hello. Margaret.

1559
01:39:00.142 --> 01:39:02.353
Do you know who I am?

1560
01:39:02.394 --> 01:39:03.938
Of course. You're Hugo.

1561
01:39:06.774 --> 01:39:08.359
Nathan.

1562
01:39:09.693 --> 01:39:13.155
Chloe. Malik.

1563
01:39:13.364 --> 01:39:15.950
Jordan. Letisha.

1564
01:39:17.076 --> 01:39:18.827
Grace.

1565
01:39:18.994 --> 01:39:20.663
Hi. Terri.

1566
01:39:20.746 --> 01:39:22.748
Kaitlyn. That's Everett.

1567
01:39:50.275 --> 01:39:52.444
I think we got it mostly right.

1568
01:39:53.821 --> 01:39:55.239
Margaret.

1569
01:39:55.447 --> 01:39:57.992
Why won't you look at me?

1570
01:39:58.117 --> 01:39:59.535
Because you're-you're the guy.

1571
01:39:59.660 --> 01:40:01.912
You're the guy
who knows everything.

1572
01:40:03.497 --> 01:40:06.333
And I'm... and I'm not ready
to know everything.

1573
01:40:08.002 --> 01:40:11.547
Including. like. why-why my mom
and dad's entire goddamn house

1574
01:40:11.588 --> 01:40:13.007
is just sitting right there!

1575
01:40:13.048 --> 01:40:16.301
What is going on?
Why are you doing this?

1576
01:40:16.427 --> 01:40:18.387
That's where I grew up.
That's where I grew up.

1577
01:40:18.512 --> 01:40:21.682
This is my life.
This is my life.

1578
01:40:21.724 --> 01:40:23.976
And this matters--
what I want. who I am.

1579
01:40:24.018 --> 01:40:27.771
not who I am as you
or him or her. but as me.

1580
01:40:31.775 --> 01:40:33.777
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

1581
01:40:33.861 --> 01:40:36.196
No. No.

1582
01:40:37.656 --> 01:40:40.451
I will not be anyone's religion.

1583
01:41:51.063 --> 01:41:52.564
My room.

1584
01:41:56.360 --> 01:41:58.278
Oh. my room.

1585
01:42:25.222 --> 01:42:27.724
Why would you build all of this?

1586
01:42:27.850 --> 01:42:30.310
To create a passage.

1587
01:42:32.271 --> 01:42:34.273
To return you to your experience

1588
01:42:34.481 --> 01:42:37.359
in the most familiar way
possible.

1589
01:42:37.442 --> 01:42:39.736
What experience?

1590
01:42:41.822 --> 01:42:44.158
The one you shared
with Margaret.

1591
01:42:45.826 --> 01:42:47.035
I shared?

1592
01:42:47.119 --> 01:42:49.329
I am not going back there.

1593
01:42:49.413 --> 01:42:51.206
-Hugo. -How much do you
remember about that night?

1594
01:42:51.331 --> 01:42:52.958
I don't remember.
and I don't want to remember.

1595
01:42:53.041 --> 01:42:54.751
and I don't want you
making me remember.

1596
01:42:54.835 --> 01:42:56.962
-Okay. Oh. my...
-Wait. Wait.

1597
01:42:57.045 --> 01:42:58.755
Wait.

1598
01:42:58.964 --> 01:43:00.841
Everything that happened to you
on the 23rd of February. 1996.

1599
01:43:00.924 --> 01:43:02.467
-is blocked. -I don't want
to know anything about it.

1600
01:43:02.551 --> 01:43:03.927
The only way for you
to know what's next

1601
01:43:04.011 --> 01:43:05.596
is to understand
what came before.

1602
01:43:05.762 --> 01:43:07.014
I don't want to talk about it.
I don't. Stop. stop. stop.

1603
01:43:07.139 --> 01:43:08.557
And then you'll know
your purpose.

1604
01:43:08.682 --> 01:43:09.808
Please don't make me.
I don't want to hear it.

1605
01:43:09.933 --> 01:43:10.767
You won't be
a passenger anymore.

1606
01:43:10.893 --> 01:43:12.769
I told you no!

1607
01:43:17.441 --> 01:43:20.819
You have the gift
but no control.

1608
01:43:20.944 --> 01:43:22.821
No understanding
of your purpose.

1609
01:43:22.988 --> 01:43:24.656
Not a clue as to
what your situation

1610
01:43:24.823 --> 01:43:27.034
will demand of you beyond today.

1611
01:43:27.159 --> 01:43:29.453
The only way for you
to acquire it

1612
01:43:29.536 --> 01:43:33.081
is to go back
to where it all began.

1613
01:43:33.207 --> 01:43:34.875
To go home.

1614
01:43:40.923 --> 01:43:45.010
And when you do. Margaret.
you'll know everything.

1615
01:43:45.093 --> 01:43:48.388
More than what was ever
humanly possible.

1616
01:44:09.618 --> 01:44:11.828
They gifted each of you.

1617
01:44:11.954 --> 01:44:14.873
Margaret. what was dormant
in you for most of your life

1618
01:44:15.040 --> 01:44:17.751
was activated only yesterday.

1619
01:44:18.710 --> 01:44:21.255
And yours. 15 years ago.

1620
01:44:21.463 --> 01:44:23.382
They gave you fluency
in the language

1621
01:44:23.423 --> 01:44:25.801
in which the book
of the universe is written:

1622
01:44:26.009 --> 01:44:27.678
mathematics.

1623
01:44:27.844 --> 01:44:31.306
Taught it to you. imbued it
so you could understand them.

1624
01:44:32.349 --> 01:44:36.520
And they imbued you
so you could understand us.

1625
01:44:38.689 --> 01:44:41.149
It's the two of you.

1626
01:44:42.734 --> 01:44:46.446
It's always been
just the two of you.

1627
01:45:08.635 --> 01:45:10.178
You can direct it

1628
01:45:10.262 --> 01:45:12.639
or feel where it wants
to take you.

1629
01:45:13.807 --> 01:45:15.809
It can find
what you're looking for.

1630
01:45:15.934 --> 01:45:18.770
It'll be an instrument
of your will.

1631
01:45:18.854 --> 01:45:21.315
But you must give yourself
over to it.

1632
01:45:22.482 --> 01:45:24.985
I'll find out
what's happening to me.

1633
01:45:27.362 --> 01:45:28.739
What?

1634
01:45:28.905 --> 01:45:30.449
It's gonna be okay.

1635
01:45:30.532 --> 01:45:32.159
I promise.

1636
01:45:49.301 --> 01:45:50.886
Whatever happens. Daniel.

1637
01:45:51.011 --> 01:45:53.096
-don't you let go.
-Don't you let go.

1638
01:45:56.183 --> 01:45:57.768
Margaret.

1639
01:46:00.145 --> 01:46:02.356
Look around the room
one more time.

1640
01:46:09.237 --> 01:46:12.657
You're a ten-year-old girl
asleep in your bed.

1641
01:46:12.783 --> 01:46:14.701
Something woke you up.
didn't it?

1642
01:46:14.743 --> 01:46:15.952
Yes.

1643
01:46:16.119 --> 01:46:17.871
So what did you do?

1644
01:46:18.789 --> 01:46:20.999
I sang my song.

1645
01:46:36.306 --> 01:46:39.935
♪ And away to his castle ♪

1646
01:46:40.102 --> 01:46:42.479
♪ We'll go ♪

1647
01:46:42.604 --> 01:46:46.274
♪ To be happy forever ♪

1648
01:46:46.483 --> 01:46:49.069
♪ I know ♪

1649
01:46:49.194 --> 01:46:53.323
♪ And the birds will sing. ♪

1650
01:47:03.667 --> 01:47:06.128
I can see them.

1651
01:47:06.169 --> 01:47:08.213
Right over there.

1652
01:47:08.380 --> 01:47:10.257
They're coming into the room.

1653
01:48:06.396 --> 01:48:08.231
No. no. no. don't go with them.

1654
01:48:08.398 --> 01:48:09.649
They're not animals.

1655
01:48:09.816 --> 01:48:11.818
Don't go with them.
They're not animals.

1656
01:48:11.902 --> 01:48:13.361
They're not animals!

1657
01:48:13.528 --> 01:48:15.155
-It's okay. It's okay.
-They're not.

1658
01:48:15.322 --> 01:48:19.242
They-they present as animals
to calm us.

1659
01:48:24.414 --> 01:48:27.000
When I walked through the glass.

1660
01:48:27.167 --> 01:48:31.171
it was like
this curtain of warm water.

1661
01:48:33.924 --> 01:48:36.259
And the snow...

1662
01:48:36.468 --> 01:48:39.763
was so warm on my feet.

1663
01:48:44.392 --> 01:48:46.478
The house.

1664
01:48:52.609 --> 01:48:55.320
"Hansel and Gretel."

1665
01:50:25.118 --> 01:50:26.786
Shh.

1666
01:50:32.584 --> 01:50:34.919
Hold my hand.

1667
01:52:11.599 --> 01:52:13.059
Whoa.

1668
01:52:14.936 --> 01:52:16.730
Whoa.

1669
01:52:54.434 --> 01:52:56.269
Hello. Hugo.

1670
01:52:59.522 --> 01:53:01.858
It's so nice
to finally know you.

1671
01:53:19.209 --> 01:53:20.794
They found us.

1672
01:53:23.296 --> 01:53:24.714
Are they out front or out back?

1673
01:53:24.923 --> 01:53:26.299
Most likely on all sides.

1674
01:53:26.508 --> 01:53:29.636
Okay. give me the. uh...
the-the-the thingy.

1675
01:53:29.677 --> 01:53:33.306
Thermal imaging showed
43 heat signatures inside here.

1676
01:53:33.473 --> 01:53:35.183
This whole area's
an industrial decay zone.

1677
01:53:35.225 --> 01:53:37.769
No other structure has
more than five people in it.

1678
01:53:45.193 --> 01:53:46.903
Hey.

1679
01:53:47.070 --> 01:53:49.489
Get on with it.

1680
01:54:33.658 --> 01:54:34.951
No one move.

1681
01:54:35.118 --> 01:54:37.328
No one make a sound.

1682
01:54:37.412 --> 01:54:38.997
They can't see us.

1683
01:54:42.458 --> 01:54:44.210
Give it to me.

1684
01:54:49.591 --> 01:54:51.509
This is not right.

1685
01:54:54.429 --> 01:54:58.224
They can't see us.
but they can see this.

1686
01:54:59.142 --> 01:55:01.769
We need to move now.

1687
01:55:01.895 --> 01:55:04.898
This is not gonna last long.
We got to go right now.

1688
01:55:15.199 --> 01:55:16.576
Look. They can't see me.

1689
01:55:16.659 --> 01:55:18.077
They can't see us. Let's go.

1690
01:55:18.161 --> 01:55:19.412
Quiet. quiet.

1691
01:55:19.621 --> 01:55:20.788
Through the back doors.
Any back door.

1692
01:55:20.914 --> 01:55:22.874
Go quiet. Go quiet.
Down the alley.

1693
01:55:22.916 --> 01:55:25.001
-Let's go. Let's go.
-Quiet.

1694
01:55:25.209 --> 01:55:27.962
Everybody. stop moving.

1695
01:55:36.137 --> 01:55:38.181
There. Look there.

1696
01:55:40.516 --> 01:55:42.101
Oh. God. I'm losing it.

1697
01:55:42.268 --> 01:55:43.937
I'm losing it.
You need to go faster.

1698
01:55:44.103 --> 01:55:45.730
-Get to the fire truck.
-I can't hold on.

1699
01:55:45.897 --> 01:55:47.023
-I can't hold...
-We got to go.

1700
01:55:47.148 --> 01:55:48.858
Stay on the light.

1701
01:55:51.903 --> 01:55:53.112
I can't hold on.

1702
01:56:03.373 --> 01:56:04.874
Let's go.

1703
01:56:07.961 --> 01:56:10.088
There. There.
Stay on the light.

1704
01:56:13.257 --> 01:56:15.635
-Stay on the light.
-The light! The light!

1705
01:56:43.079 --> 01:56:45.248
Hang on.
Grab ahold of something.

1706
01:57:06.352 --> 01:57:08.354
Which one do we follow?!

1707
01:57:09.522 --> 01:57:11.482
There's only one place
she's going.

1708
01:57:27.040 --> 01:57:28.499
Urgent measures are being

1709
01:57:28.583 --> 01:57:30.376
implemented across
the European Union.

1710
01:57:30.585 --> 01:57:32.170
where the Schengen Code
has been invoked.

1711
01:57:32.336 --> 01:57:33.629
closing all national borders...

1712
01:57:33.838 --> 01:57:36.674
-I...
-I know. I know.

1713
01:57:36.758 --> 01:57:38.968
...for an imminent
inbound missile attack.

1714
01:57:39.093 --> 01:57:40.845
In North Korea.
a second breakaway faction

1715
01:57:41.012 --> 01:57:43.181
has announced
it has taken control

1716
01:57:43.306 --> 01:57:44.724
of as many as four
military bases

1717
01:57:44.766 --> 01:57:46.601
and confirm troop rollouts
from Pyongyang.

1718
01:57:46.809 --> 01:57:47.852
Where's Clay?

1719
01:57:48.061 --> 01:57:49.604
Taran Davies at the BBC

1720
01:57:49.729 --> 01:57:51.481
has a contact inside
the Korean Central News Agency.

1721
01:57:51.606 --> 01:57:54.192
the official news agency
of the North Korean government.

1722
01:57:54.358 --> 01:57:55.651
and had this to say earlier...

1723
01:57:55.777 --> 01:57:56.944
What are you doing here?

1724
01:57:57.028 --> 01:57:58.654
You should be in the hospital.

1725
01:58:00.073 --> 01:58:01.908
What...

1726
01:58:02.867 --> 01:58:04.577
Duncan is such a good boy.

1727
01:58:04.660 --> 01:58:07.830
and he needs you there tomorrow.
even if he can't say it.

1728
01:58:13.252 --> 01:58:15.046
I'm going on air
at the anchor desk

1729
01:58:15.171 --> 01:58:17.465
to deliver a special report.

1730
01:58:17.673 --> 01:58:20.426
O... o-okay.

1731
01:58:20.551 --> 01:58:21.719
Okay.

1732
01:58:21.928 --> 01:58:23.387
How do I get
to the control room?

1733
01:58:23.554 --> 01:58:25.056
I need to get
to the loading dock.

1734
01:58:25.223 --> 01:58:26.432
This is Daniel. This is Hugo.

1735
01:58:26.599 --> 01:58:27.975
-Clay. can you help us?
-Of course.

1736
01:58:28.101 --> 01:58:30.311
Uh. I don't know
what's happening. but come on.

1737
01:58:30.436 --> 01:58:31.938
Hailey.

1738
01:58:32.021 --> 01:58:34.690
The loading dock is
the second sign to the right.

1739
01:58:34.899 --> 01:58:36.526
What exactly is happening?

1740
01:58:36.651 --> 01:58:37.819
What's up?

1741
01:58:37.944 --> 01:58:39.237
Margaret's taking over
the anchor desk.

1742
01:58:39.362 --> 01:58:40.279
-What?
-Help her.

1743
01:58:40.363 --> 01:58:42.073
-Okay.
-The control room.

1744
01:58:42.240 --> 01:58:43.950
Why am I doing this? Come on.

1745
01:58:44.117 --> 01:58:45.785
The control room's upstairs.
Just follow me.

1746
01:58:48.079 --> 01:58:50.289
I called the police about him.

1747
01:58:51.499 --> 01:58:54.210
Maria and I moved out.
We're with my sister now.

1748
01:58:55.253 --> 01:58:57.171
-She's good.
-Good.

1749
01:58:57.213 --> 01:58:59.966
-Thank you.
-Of course.

1750
01:59:01.551 --> 01:59:03.136
Do you want makeup?

1751
01:59:04.011 --> 01:59:05.138
Yeah.

1752
01:59:17.275 --> 01:59:19.443
What's going on down there?
I had to hard-cut to commercial.

1753
01:59:19.527 --> 01:59:20.820
-Special report.
-What report?

1754
01:59:20.945 --> 01:59:22.572
-Who's this guy?
-He's gonna upload.

1755
01:59:22.780 --> 01:59:24.282
Do exactly what he says.

1756
01:59:24.407 --> 01:59:26.159
I'm putting it directly
on your server.

1757
01:59:26.242 --> 01:59:27.785
-This your coffee?
-Yes.

1758
01:59:28.786 --> 01:59:30.371
Where's playback?

1759
01:59:30.538 --> 01:59:32.331
-Uh. that's me.
-Stand by. It's kind of a lot.

1760
01:59:32.498 --> 01:59:34.917
TD. what are
your playback channels?

1761
01:59:35.126 --> 01:59:36.752
They're in W. X. Y and Z.

1762
01:59:36.961 --> 01:59:38.504
We're gonna load up all of them.

1763
01:59:38.629 --> 01:59:40.506
It's coming in raw.
so you got to mix it.

1764
01:59:40.548 --> 01:59:42.675
And. hey. no tape delay.
I mean. not a frame.

1765
01:59:42.800 --> 01:59:44.302
Go straight to the feed
and leave it open.

1766
01:59:44.385 --> 01:59:45.928
Director. no cuts.

1767
01:59:46.053 --> 01:59:47.346
This plays itself.

1768
01:59:47.555 --> 01:59:48.848
It's gonna go outside
your market fast.

1769
01:59:48.973 --> 01:59:50.433
How do I route
from the affiliate server

1770
01:59:50.600 --> 01:59:52.018
so network has access?

1771
01:59:52.101 --> 01:59:53.519
You really think network's
gonna bump World War III

1772
01:59:53.644 --> 01:59:55.062
for whatever you got?

1773
01:59:55.229 --> 01:59:56.647
You bet they will.

1774
01:59:57.815 --> 01:59:59.233
-Hey. Shea.
-Yeah.

1775
01:59:59.442 --> 02:00:00.818
